TITLE: Biden says hate ‘remains a stain on the soul of America’ after Buffalo mass shooting
SUMMARY: President Biden said hate "remains a stain on the soul of America" after an alleged white supremacist gunned down 10 people Saturday afternoon.

TITLE: Biden administration to remove 5 terror groups from blacklist
SUMMARY: The Biden administration plans to remove five terror organizations from a federal blacklist.

TITLE: Oklahoma Gov. defends strict abortion law, addresses whether 'super liberal' tribal clinics may use loophole
SUMMARY: Oklahoma Gov. Kevin Stitt pushed back against critics of his state's abortion law, which bans abortion when there is a fetal heartbeat, typically six weeks into pregnancy, while recognizing that there is a gaping loophole.

TITLE: Will the Supreme Court release a Roe v. Wade decision this week?
SUMMARY: The Supreme Court will issue a batch of opinions on an unknown number of cases Monday, but the highly-anticipated decision that could determine the fate of abortion protections is likely weeks away, according to judicial experts.

TITLE: Pelosi says ‘creature’ Trump made Supreme Court ‘dangerous,’ ‘anti-freedom’
SUMMARY: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi, D-Calif., on Sunday responded to criticism that Democrats should have been better prepared for the conservative-led attack on abortion rights, saying, "Who would ever [have] suspected that a creature like Donald Trump would become president of the United States?"

TITLE: Is Trump faceoff with Pence in Georgia GOP gubernatorial showdown an early 2024 skirmish?
SUMMARY: Is the Donald Trump face off with former Vice President Mike Pence in Georgia's GOP gubernatorial showdown an early 2024 skirmish?

TITLE: Dr. Oz says 2015 tweet should disqualify Barnette from Republican primary: 'reprehensible'
SUMMARY: Republican candidate Dr. Mehmet Oz said fellow candidate Kathy Barnette should be disqualified from Tuesday's primary election after she criticized his religion in a tweet more than seven years ago.

TITLE: Small groups of protesters show up at Supreme Court justices' homes to push for Roe v. Wade
SUMMARY: Small groups of protesters arrived at several homes of Supreme Court justices Saturday evening capping a day of rallies for Roe v. Wade, the 1973 case that granted legal protection for most abortions.

TITLE: Lawmakers react to Buffalo shooting that left 10 dead, 3 injured
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden, New York Gov. Kathy Hochul, and local lawmakers have reacted to the shooting incident in Buffalo Saturday afternoon that left 10 people and injured 13 others.

TITLE: Biden says he, first lady are ‘praying’ for victims in Buffalo shooting; condemns possible hate crime
SUMMARY: President Biden condemned the deadly shooting in Buffalo on Saturday.

TITLE: Judge blocks Alabama law criminalizing the prescription of puberty blockers for transgender youth
SUMMARY: A federal judge blocked an Alabama law that had made it a felony for doctors to provide puberty blockers and hormone treatment to children.

TITLE: Heritage president calls Ukrainian aid ‘typical Washington game,’ avoids effective Russian ‘deterrence’
SUMMARY: The president of one of the nation’s most prominent conservative think tanks has come out against the $40 billion aid package for Ukraine currently being debated in Congress.

TITLE: Pro-choice activist group Ruth Sent Us says TikTok account was 'permanently banned'
SUMMARY: The far-left abortion activist group Ruth Sent Us says it's main TikTok account, which at one point had more than 20,000 followers, had been 'permanently banned' from the platform.

TITLE: Eric Adams blasts pro-life 'radical extremists,' says women have 'right' to abortions up until day of birth
SUMMARY: New York City Mayor Eric Adams spoke out against anti-abortion "radicals" and said there should be "no" limitations on abortion.

TITLE: Border Patrol nabs slew of sex offenders, gang members as border crisis picks up
SUMMARY: Border Patrol agents have apprehended a number of sex offenders and gang members coming across the border in the last week, amid a broader migrant surge that is overwhelming officials at the border.

TITLE: White House, Twitter silent on why tweet with vaccine misinformation hasn't been taken down
SUMMARY: The White House is facing backlash after it falsely claimed in a tweet this week that "there was no vaccine available" for COVID-19 when Joe Biden took office last year, but Twitter, along with the White House remain silent on why the that claim remains on the platform with no "misinformation" warning label.

TITLE: Texas to provide Mexican state with razor wire, training for border security
SUMMARY: The unprecedented agreement between Texas and the Mexican state of Coahuila -- which is situated across from Eagle Pass -- will involve Texas providing the Mexican authorities with c-wire (concertina/razor wire) and training on its deployment.

TITLE: Pro-choice activists descend on DC, vow to be 'ungovernable' as they protest draft Supreme Court opinion
SUMMARY: Thousands of pro-choice activists from different corners in America descended on Washington, D.C., on Saturday for the "Bans Off Our Bodies" event organized by a coalition of groups including Planned Parenthood and the Women's March.

TITLE: Sens. Schumer, Gillibrand join pro-choice NYC protests, call for Senate to codify Roe into law
SUMMARY: The protest also featured Mayor Eric Adams, who said he does not support limits on abortion and that "women should have a right to choose for their bodies."

TITLE: Pro-choice protesters gather for 'Bans Off Our Bodies' marches across country
SUMMARY: Protesters gathered in New York, Washington, D.C. and other U.S. cities Saturday to march for legal protections of abortion and to protest the potential end of Roe v. Wade.
